chunk_content: • A helpful way to assess OVC_HIVSTAT performance is to create a “known status proxy” category of known status/risk (by combining those reported positive, negative, and those who have been risk assessed and found to not require a test) and compare this with the OVC_SERV <18 years of age or 18-20 years of age “OVC Comprehensive” disaggregates. These analyses encourage programs to actively follow-up on all instances of “HIV status unknown” by targeting instances of missing data, nondisclosure, and issues with reporting timing. The primary focus remains on OVC Comprehensive program participants <18 years of age, but the inclusion of participants 18-20 years of age analysis allows implementing partners to have a comprehensive understanding of the status of ALL the OVC in their programs. • This indicator is a subset of the OVC_SERV Comprehensive program.
